<h3>Assignments</h3>

	<p>
		Assignments are in-depth, self-directed assignments used to explore and execute a non-academic design problem or series of problems. Significant research and development is required. To succeed, combine learned mechanics and principles, review and expand upon content and individual artistic expression.
	</p>

	<p>
		You will create your own artwork responding to your research and learned skills with creative freedom.
	</p>

	<p>
		There are <strong>10 assignments</strong> for this course worth <strong>10 points each</strong>. The midterm project is worth <strong> 15 points</strong>. The final project is worth <strong>30 points</strong>. Each assignment will expand the studentâ€™s knowledge of an important aspect of Adobe Photoshop. Assignments are graded on application of subject matter, appropriate use of the software and creativity.
	</p>

